abstract: The Chinese e-commerce reported a staggering $2 billion of profit on $2.5 billion in revenue for its most recent quarter, as more details emerged about its I.P.O. aimed for mid-September.
snippet: The Chinese e-commerce reported a staggering $2 billion of profit on $2.5 billion in revenue for its most recent quarter, as more details emerged about its I.P.O. aimed for mid-September.
lead_paragraph: With less than a month before its initial public offering, the Alibaba Group is intent on showing just how profitable — and focused on mobile — it truly is.

headline.main: Mobile Sales Lift Alibaba Profit Nearly Threefold, Ahead of I.P.O.

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced
